laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Magnetic resonance imaging of the shoulder
laboratory_examinations.findings: Demonstrated distension of the glenohumeral joint with a low signal on T1-weighted images, a high signal on T2-weighted images, and uniformly bright enhancement on post-gadolinium-injection images.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: At five years after the initial presentation, no substantial change was noted.
